-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Credicorp, Ferreyros, Pomalca, Relapasa
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2011-12-15T21:37:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/peru-stocks-candente-credicorp-ferreyros-pomalca-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first session in seven,
gaining 0.4 percent to 19,389.82. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index 
climbed 0.6 percent to 2,474.88.  Industrial and banking shares rebounded after U.S. stocks
gained, said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, rose 4.1 percent to 51 centimos.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services company, gained 2 percent
to $104.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1)  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of
Repsol YPF SA, climbed 1.1 percent to 89 centimos.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
advanced 1.8 percent to 2.30 soles.  Mining stocks gained after metals advanced in  London .  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, rose 10 percent to 11 cents.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining exploration company
with operations in Peru, advanced 7.7 percent to 98 cents.  Cia.
de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN)  , the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, climbed 2 percent to $38.25 after the
government agreed to resume talks with protesters opposing the
company’s Minas Conga project.  Southern Copper Corp.  (SCCO PE),
Peru’s biggest copper producer, rose 0.8 percent to $29.14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
